text: Those who are saying this movie looks bad don't know what they're talking about. This movie was obviously created to appeal to kids and young teens - as they bring a legend with a modern twist to life. Honestly, I think that this looks pretty good, generically speaking. Have you seen most of the movies they're coming out with? I mean, a Teen Titans Go movie? In THEATERS? That, to me, sounds stupid. On the other hand, this movie looks fantastic. It's not every day they release a trailer for a movie that's a twist on legend/lore, especially when it comes to companies like 20th Century Fox. I think it'll do fairly well when it comes to younger audiences, and I, for one, am going to be apart of that audience. There's some sarcastic humor in it (the part where the teacher allows the kids to use swords and to fight instead of classes...if only), and I enjoy that. Personally, I'm pretty excited about this <3
